Vendored third-party component: FamDB
=====================================

This directory is a bundled (vendored) copy of FamDB, the Dfam Consortium's
tool for querying FamDB-format (.h5) transposable-element databases.

    Upstream : https://github.com/Dfam-consortium/FamDB
    Version  : 2.0.5
    License  : CC0 1.0 Universal (public-domain dedication)
               https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/
    Authors  : Anthony Gray, Jeb Rosen, and the Dfam consortium

FamDB is released into the public domain under CC0; it is redistributed here
under those terms. See famdb.py and README.md for the original notices.

How RepLibBuilder uses it
-------------------------
RepLibBuilder calls `famdb.py ... families -f embl` to extract curated Dfam
families for a given NCBI taxon from a user-supplied, pre-built Dfam .h5
database (see ../rating_module/dfam_fetcher.py).

Trimmed for distribution
------------------------
The following were removed because they are NOT needed for the query/`families`
path RepLibBuilder uses (they are inputs only for *building* a FamDB file):

    - RepeatPeps.lib   (~18 MB RepeatMasker peptide library)
    - the upstream .git history

Everything required to query a pre-built Dfam .h5 is retained and unmodified.
